      "content": "calling them \"short-term fears\" and \"talking points\" makes it sound like their concerns aren't actually valid though. if a town loses its main industry and the lights go out because the grid can't handle the solar, that's a pretty big deal. doesn't that side have a legitimate point about the stability of the state's economy?",
